        * <http://stackoverflow.com/questions/12925802/run-a-node-js-script-with-command-line-arguments/12925835#12925835>
        * If you want to do more sophisticated stuff, the following modules are really helpful:
            * [node-optimist](https://github.com/substack/node-optimist) by James Halliday aka substack
            * [commander](https://github.com/visionmedia/commander.js) by TJ Holowaychuk -- best of lot
            * [nopt](https://github.com/isaacs/nopt) by Isaac Schlueter
        * And for fun
            * [cli-table](https://github.com/isaacs/nopt) by Guillermo Rauch -- console tables
            * [node-multimeter](https://github.com/isaacs/nopt) by substack -- progress bars
            * [colors](https://github.com/Marak/colors.js) by Marak -- colored console output
        * one more
            * [nconf](https://github.com/flatiron/nconf)
        * and simply
            ```
            // print process.argv
            process.argv.forEach(function (val, index, array) {
              console.log(index + ': ' + val);
            });
            ```
    - options or commands
        - all, tcsh, bash, zsh
        - match one|all

- shell script for php
    - lookup `$*` or find something that passes all arguments into script  
        - $@ is your huckleberry
        ```
        #!/usr/bin/env sh
        php "$@"
        echo "\nDo you want to reset this terminal?"
        select yn in "Yes" "No"; do
            case $yn in
                Yes ) reset; break;;
                No ) break;;
            esac
        done
        ```
- `php -r 'print_r($argv);'`
