* mysql install
```
==> /usr/local/Cellar/mysql/5.6.10/bin/mysql_install_db --verbose --user=anand --basedir=/usr/local/Cel
==> Caveats
A "/etc/my.cnf" from another install may interfere with a Homebrew-built
server starting up correctly.

To connect:
    mysql -uroot

To have launchd start mysql at login:
    ln -sfv /usr/local/opt/mysql/*.plist ~/Library/LaunchAgents
Then to load mysql now:
    launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/homebrew.mxcl.mysql.plist
Or, if you don't want/need launchctl, you can just run:
    mysql.server start
Change root password:
    /usr/local/mysql/bin/mysqladmin -u root password 'yourpasswordhere'
```
* php 5.2.17 install
```
==> ./configure --prefix=/usr/local/Cellar/php52/5.2.17 --localstatedir=/usr/local/var --sysconfdir=/us
==> make
==> make install
==> Caveats
To enable PHP in Apache add the following to httpd.conf and restart Apache:
    LoadModule php5_module    /usr/local/opt/php52/libexec/apache2/libphp5.so

The php.ini file can be found in:
    /usr/local/etc/php/5.2/php.ini

‚ú©‚ú©‚ú©‚ú© PEAR ‚ú©‚ú©‚ú©‚ú©

If PEAR complains about permissions, 'fix' the default PEAR permissions and config:
    chmod -R ug+w /usr/local/Cellar/php52/5.2.17/lib/php
    pear config-set php_ini /usr/local/etc/php/5.2/php.ini

‚ú©‚ú©‚ú©‚ú© Extensions ‚ú©‚ú©‚ú©‚ú©

If you are having issues with custom extension compiling, ensure that this php is
in your PATH:
    PATH="$(brew --prefix josegonzalez/php/php52)/bin:$PATH"

PHP52 Extensions will always be compiled against this PHP. Please install them
using --without-homebrew-php to enable compiling against system PHP.
==> Summary
üç∫  /usr/local/Cellar/php52/5.2.17: 444 files, 20M, built in 11.7 minutes
```

